dummyism
Homonym Number:
Word Class:noun
Sense Number: 1
Definition:the use of others to buy land for oneself. [an unofficial situation of the 1800s and early 1900s where farmers used other purchasers to help them acquire land.]
Origin:[none]
Register:
Register 2:
Flag: Farm Words
Domain:Rural
Region:[none]
See:
Pronunciation:
Notes:
