Source: Hawera Star
Author:
Vol / Page: 9
Edition:
Quote: The Otago Daily Times suggests that a Royal Commission should be appointed to investigate charges of dummyism in respect to land recently leased.
Notes:

Date: 8/6/1883
Source: Hawera Star
Author:
Vol / Page: 2
Edition:
Quote: At the dummyism inquiry today, one man, named Kenneth Williamson, a shepherd in the employ of Messrs Gellibrand and Smith, and who was a purchaser at the land sale, said he had been "sounded" as to becoming a purchaser, and had been given to understand that unless he took up a particular section he must shift elsewhere.
Notes:

Date: 0/12/1892
Source: NZ Farmer
Author:
Vol / Page: 493
Edition:
Quote: A gross case of dummyism is said to exist in Hawke's Bay and steps will probably be taken to bring it before the public.
Notes:

Date: 6/8/1900
Source: Hawera Star
Author:
Vol / Page: 2
Edition:
Quote: If two or three families select adjoining blocks, a ring fence can be run around the whole allotment. One of the first and most obvious objectives is that the system would afford an easy method of dummyism. Members of a family might be used to "dummy" for their rich relatives.
